{
  "files": [
    {
      "repo": "sg-evals/expressjs-express",
      "path": "lib/request.js"
    },
    {
      "repo": "sg-evals/expressjs-express",
      "path": "test/req.host.js"
    },
    {
      "repo": "sg-evals/expressjs-express",
      "path": "History.md"
    }
  ],
  "text": "The deprecated `req.host` property is referenced in three source files in sg-evals/expressjs-express:\n\n1. **lib/request.js** (lines 452, 454, 456): Contains the actual definition and implementation of the deprecated `req.host` property. Line 454 defines the getter using `defineGetter(req, 'host', deprecate.function(...))` which wraps the property with a deprecation warning. The property returns `this.hostname` at line 455, with a deprecation message \"req.host: Use req.hostname instead\" at line 456.\n\n2. **test/req.host.js**: Contains comprehensive test cases for the `req.host` property across multiple scenarios (lines 12, 25, 39, 51, 64, 80, 96, 112, 128, 145). Tests verify behavior including stripping port numbers, handling IPv6 hosts, and respecting the \"trust proxy\" setting. All references verified to be `req.host` and not `req.hostname`.\n\n3. **History.md**: Contains changelog entries documenting the history of `req.host` (lines 799, 1284, 1286, 1436, 1653, 2368, 2514, 2552, 2726). Key entries include: the addition of `req.host` (line 2726), its deprecation in favor of `req.hostname` (lines 1284-1286), and various bug fixes related to `req.host` handling (IPv6 support, trust proxy, X-Forwarded-Host support).\n\nAll references were verified to use `req.host` specifically as the standalone deprecated property, not as a substring of `req.hostname`."
}

